President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. Jennifer D. Nordquist is nominated to be the Executive Director of the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development. She currently serves as Chief of Staff at the Council of Economic Advisers and has held various positions in government and academia. John Linder is nominated to be the Representative of the United States of America to the Association of Southeast Asian Nations. He is a former United States Representative from Georgia and has experience in Congress and as a small business owner. John McLeod Barger is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Governors of the United States Postal Service. David Bernhardt is nominated to be Secretary of the Interior, a position he currently serves in an acting capacity. He has a long history of working at the Department of the Interior and has been confirmed by the Senate twice before for positions within the department.